[SN]TITLE[SN]
Barnsley Council apology for bin men's 'bad behaviour'

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A council has been forced to apologise after CCTV footage emerged of bin men throwing bags of rubbish and a wheelie bin around.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Cheryl Parker, 45, wondered why the bins where she lives in Prince Arthur Street, Barnsley, were all over the place and so checked her CCTV.
The video of the bin men's actions has been widely shared on social media.
Barnsley council said the behaviour was unacceptable and an investigation would be carried out.
