A council spokesman said: "Barnsley Council aims to deliver a consistently high standard of service and this clearly falls short.
"This behaviour is totally unacceptable and a full investigation will be carried out.
"We thank the resident for getting in touch and apologise for the level of service she received and any distress caused."
